      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 526: The cached cameraPosition is set to .front before the switch succeeds and is never restored on failure. If switching fails, the service state says the front camera is active while the capture session may still be using the previous camera, which can break later orientation/device-position decisions. Update cached state only after switchCamera(toPosition:) completes successfully, or roll it back in onError.\n```suggestion\nself.camera.switchCamera(toPosition: .front)\n    .subscribe(onCompleted: { [weak self] in\n        self?.cameraPosition \u003d .front\n        self?.updateCachedOrientation()\n    }, onError: { error in\n        print(error)\n    })\n    .disposed(by: self.disposeBag)\n```",
