      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 695: resetCameraToFrontForCapture() updates cameraPosition/orientation and starts an asynchronous camera switch, but startCapture() immediately continues to start capture. This can expose stale state or start capture before the front-camera switch has completed if startCapturing() is not strictly serialized behind the same sessionQueue work. Move the capture start into the switch completion path, or return a Completable from resetCameraToFrontForCapture() and chain the quality/orientation/start logic after it completes.\n```suggestion\nprivate func resetCameraToFrontForCapture() -\u003e Completable {\n    self.cameraPosition \u003d .front\n    self.updateCachedOrientation()\n    return self.camera.switchCamera(toPosition: .front)\n}\n```\nThen call camera.startCapturing() from the subscription\u0027s onCompleted handler.",
